President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to the United States Sentencing Commission. Judge William H. Pryor Jr. of Alabama is nominated to serve as the Chairman of the Commission. He currently serves as a Circuit Judge of the United States Court of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit and as Acting Chairman of the Sentencing Commission. Judge Luis Felipe Restrepo of Pennsylvania is nominated to serve as a Commissioner of the Commission. He currently serves as a Circuit Judge of the United States Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit. Judge Henry E. Hudson of Virginia is nominated to serve as a Commissioner of the Commission. He currently serves as a United States District Judge for the Eastern District of Virginia. William Graham Otis of Virginia is also nominated to serve as a Commissioner of the Commission. He currently serves as an Adjunct Professor of Law at Georgetown University Law Center.